<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="164" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,152,359]" pageId="15" pageNumber="164">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,225,251]" pageId="15" pageNumber="164">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[620,723,225,251]" pageId="15" pageNumber="164">lectotype</typeStatus>
appears to have a very large gonopore; this is, based on other specimens of this species examined, because the male genitalia had dried out, and the membranous area surrounding the gonopore had consequently retracted toward the lateral margins. Images of a specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[1197,1338,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[1197,1338,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="164">H. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the gonopore of usual size is given in Perkins (in press).
</paragraph>
